- The integer result is the length of the longest valid substring of the string `word`.
- A substring is considered valid if none of its substrings are present in the list of strings `forbidden`.
- The length of the string `word` is greater than or equal to 1 and is less than or equal to 100000.
- The length of the list of strings `forbidden` is greater than or equal to 1 and is less than or equal to 100000.
- Each string in the list of strings `forbidden` has a length greater than or equal to 1 and is less than or equal to 10.
- The characters in the string `word` and the strings in the list `forbidden` are all lowercase English letters.